{"name": "finufft", "metadata": {"name": "finufft", "version": "2.3.0", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: Apache Software License", "Operating System :: MacOS :: MacOS X", "Operating System :: Microsoft :: Windows", "Operating System :: POSIX :: Linux", "Programming Language :: C++", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["numpy"], "summary": "Python interface to FINUFFT", "upload_time": 1725965432}, "documentation": ["# Flatiron Institute Nonuniform Fast Fourier Transform library: FINUFFT\n\nPrincipal author **Alex H. Barnett**, main co-developers Jeremy F. Magland, Ludvig af Klinteberg, Yu-hsuan \"Melody\" Shih, Andrea Malleo, Libin Lu, Joakim And\u00e9n, Marco Barbone, and Robert Blackwell.\n\nThis package provides a Python interface to the CPU library, enabling fast computation of nonuniform discrete Fourier transforms to specified precision in one, two, and three dimensions.\nIt supports transforms of type 1 (nonuniform to uniform), type 2 (uniform to nonuniform) and type 3 (nonuniform to nonuniform).\nFor more information, see the [online documentation](https://finufft.readthedocs.io/en/latest/python.html).\n\nIf you find FINUFFT useful in your work, please cite this package and our paper:\n\n    A parallel non-uniform fast Fourier transform library based on an ``exponential of semicircle'' kernel.\n    A. H. Barnett, J. F. Magland, and L. af Klinteberg.\n    SIAM J. Sci. Comput. 41(5), C479\u2013C504 (2019).\n"], "modules": [{"name": "python.finufft.finufft", "documentation": ["The Python interface to FINUFFT is divided into two parts: the simple\ninterface (through the `nufft*` functions) and the more advanced plan\ninterface (through the `Plan` class). The former allows the user to perform\nan NUFFT in a single call while the latter allows for more efficient reuse of\nresources when the same NUFFT is applied several times to different data by\nsaving FFTW plans, sorting the nonuniform points, and so on.\n"], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "python.finufft.finufft.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "python.finufft.finufft.nufft1d1", "xref": {"fqname": "finufft._interfaces.nufft1d1", "project": null}}, {"name": "python.finufft.finufft.nufft1d2", "xref": {"fqname": "finufft._interfaces.nufft1d2", "project": null}}, {"name": "python.finufft.finufft.nufft1d3", "xref": {"fqname": "finufft._interfaces.nufft1d3", "project": null}}, {"name": "python.finufft.finufft.nufft2d1", "xref": {"fqname": "finufft._interfaces.nufft2d1", "project": null}}, {"name": "python.finufft.finufft.nufft2d2", "xref": {"fqname": "finufft._interfaces.nufft2d2", "project": null}}, {"name": "python.finufft.finufft.nufft2d3", "xref": {"fqname": "finufft._interfaces.nufft2d3", "project": null}}, {"name": "python.finufft.finufft.nufft3d1", "xref": {"fqname": "finufft._interfaces.nufft3d1", "project": null}}, {"name": "python.finufft.finufft.nufft3d2", "xref": {"fqname": "finufft._interfaces.nufft3d2", "project": null}}, {"name": "python.finufft.finufft.nufft3d3", "xref": {"fqname": "finufft._interfaces.nufft3d3", "project": null}}, {"name": "python.finufft.finufft.Plan", "xref": {"fqname": "finufft._interfaces.Plan", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "python.finufft.finufft._finufft", "documentation": ["Adapted from cufinufft python interface using ctypes.\nThis file contains low level python bindings for the finufft libraries.\nSeperate bindings are provided for single and double precision libraries,\ndifferentiated by 'f' suffix.", "!/usr/bin/env python"], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "python.finufft.finufft._finufft.c_int_p", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "python.finufft.finufft._finufft.c_float_p", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "python.finufft.finufft._finufft.c_double_p", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "python.finufft.finufft._finufft.c_longlong_p", "t